Young people can run faster if they are alone. Older people are slower, but can go farther.
>A Luo proverb used in East Africa from Sudan to Tanzania says, "A young man can run fast when he is alone. Alone a youth runs fast, with an elder. Alone a youth runs fast, with an elder slow, but together they go far.
